    "author_channel_id": "UCzoiKHd_m_INw7IRqGZEX5A",
    "text": "4:10 actually, while fuzzy skin can give you a fluffy APPEARANCE, it usually feels pretty rough. However, if you use it like I do (by turning the settings down just a bit) and printing it just on the outer surfaces of say, cases or enclosures you will get a very touch pleasing  texture. A texture that seems somewhat like a lightly roughened injection molded part. For instance like a hand grip.",
